channel.title: Who Watches the Star Trek Men!
channel.description:
:stuck_out_tongue:
[url]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WTqJjwJxlm0[/url]
Well saw the movies twice two days in a row, I really though it was an entertaining movie, one of the better movies of the year for entertainment value, hardcore fans will be disappointed for sure but who gives a fuck, I want to be entertained.
The CGI is amazing, the warp effect is fantastic, explaining the idea of a paradox so they can make shit up for the rest of movies, acceptable. Zachary Quinto as Spock, brilliant casting, Chris Pine, is ok in his role. Eric Bana is a good bad guy but not the best sadly. Old Shock = good space battles were good but could have been better and etc
dislikes, didn't like chekov in this, Simon Pegg's scenes seem tacked on for some reason to me. and what the hell was with that little guy that was with Scottie...
